review_text:
Wonderful hotel with super luxury services but to which I can not give 5 for some negatives:
- absolutely insufficient supply of gluten-free products for breakfast at both Rise and Spago;
- the food in the famous pool on the 57th floor was poor (soft and cold fries, Caesar salad practically made only with lettuce, club sandwich stubby etc);
- room from over 2000 euros per night on a low floor and street view;
- housekeeping that often did not do turndown service.
It is undoubtedly a fantastic resort but I cannot be satisfied with the price paid.

