review_text:
Strengths:

- Very beautiful and iconic hotel (the pool on the 57th floor is really beautiful);
- Many shopping options in the area called Shops Marina Bay Sands;
- Polite and helpful check-in staff;
- Large room with a beautiful view of the city (we stayed on floor 38).

Negative points:

- Very small gym for the hotel's standard (it is located outside the hotel, close to the shopping mall). Few equipment options and insufficient treadmills for a hotel that has more than 2000 rooms;
- Staff who collect and deliver bags are terrible (they forgot to take one of our bags to the room, it took a while to find it);
- Bad and expensive breakfast (tasteless and poor quality bread and sweets due to being made on a large scale).

